<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Confirm Verification - MIT IdentiBot</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/static/main.css">
</head>
<body>
<div>
    <div class="centered">
        <h1>Are you sure that you want to link your Kerberos account to this Discord account?</h1>
        <p><b>Your Kerberos identity can verify <em>only one</em> Discord account.</b> If you continue:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Your Kerberos identity, {{sessionInformation.linksInProgress.petrock.email}}, will be linked to the Discord account @{{sessionInformation.discordUser.username}}.</b> <i>You cannot undo this action without assistance</i>.</li>
            <li><b>Your nickname in some Discord servers will be updated to &ldquo;{{newServerNickname}}&rdquo;</b> You will still be able to change your nickname if you have permission to do so.</li>
            <li><b>Server moderators with a verified MIT affiliation will be able to look up your name, email, and MIT ID card photo.</b> You can disable moderator access to your ID card photo using the <b style="color: #5865F2;">/usersettings allowmoderatoridphotolookup</b> Discord command.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="text-centered">
            <a href="/verification/confirm/petrock">
                <button class="confirm-button">
                    Verify @{{sessionInformation.discordUser.username}}
                </button>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
